# clamdscan

> A command-line virus scanner using the ClamAV Daemon
> More information: https://www.clamav.net

- Scan a file or directory for vulnerabilities:

`clamdscan {file something|path something}`

- Scan data from stdin:

`{any something} | clamdscan -`

- Scan the current directory and output only infected files:

`clamdscan --infected`

- Output the scan report to a log file:

`clamdscan --log {file something: log}`

- Move infected files to a specific directory:

`clamdscan --move {directory something: quarantine}`

- Remove infected files:

`clamdscan --remove`

- Use multiple threads to scan a directory:

`clamdscan --multiscan`

- Pass the file descriptor instead of streaming the file to the daemon:

`clamdscan --fdpass`
